<HEAD>ABC's `Roseanne' Takes First in Television Ratings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Summer reruns, topped by the <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> comedy hit `` Roseanne,'' beat out original programming in the latest Nielsen ratings. Two other <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> shows _ `` Wonder Years'' and `` Who's the Boss'' _ were next in the ratings for the week ended Aug. 6, but the network remained in third place. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> each finished the week with four shows in the Top 10, but it was <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> which gained a 59th consecutive victory. `` Roseanne,'' snubbed last week in the Emmy nominations, supplanted <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Cheers'' in the top spot. The <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> barroom antics fell to fourth place, tying with <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Coach.'' Original programming fared poorly in the ratings, despite coming amid summer doldrums. The <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> news </ORGANIZATION> program `` Yesterday, Today & amp; Tomorrow'' made its debut in a tie for 19th place with <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Full House.'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s much-touted `` PrimeTime Live'' was in 37th place The NBC summer series `` 13 East'' dropped from 10th place last week to 35th. Another NBC summer show, `` Knight & amp; <PERSON> Daye </PERSON>,'' remained in the middle of the ratings in a four-way tie for 50th place. <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s summertime jump in the ratings has apparently bottomed out. `` Married ... With Children'' dropped to 38th place, `` Totally Hidden Video'' was 46th and `` <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Most Wanted'' in the four-way tie for 50th place. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> survey with an average of 10.5. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> was second with 9.4 and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> third with 9.2. For the season to date, from Sept. 19, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> had 14.7, <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 11.8 and CBS 11.7. The ratings are the percentage of the 90.4 million homes with televisions in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The share is the percentage of sets in use. Here are the Top 10: <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Roseanne,'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Wonder Years,'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Who's the Boss?,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Cheers `` and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Coach'' tied, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Golden Girls,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` <PERSON> Perry </PERSON> <PERSON> Mason </PERSON>: The Case of the Lost Love'' and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>' `` Murder, She Wrote'' tied, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Empty Nest'' and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>' `` Designing Women'' tied. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> claimed first place among the nightly news shows. The ratings: <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 9.4, <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> 9.1, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> 8.6.
