<HEAD>Oliver North Begins Community Service in Anti-Drug Program</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LEE BYRD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Former Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> North </PERSON> is beginning his service as a draftee in the war against narcotics by helping reformed drug dealers and other underworld figures to repay their crimes. The national security aide who directed some of the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration's boldest covert ventures abroad now will be plotting forays much nearer the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> as five men calling themselves the `` New Pied Pipers'' attempt to clean up their old neighborhoods in the capital. North will `` most definitely'' be given a tour of the worst drug neighborhoods, but he wo n't be active on the streets, program coordinator <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said Tuesday. `` He's not a street-wise individual _ we know that. His element is administration.'' North, conscripted into the drug battle by the judge who sentenced him in the Iran-Contra trial, began his orientation Monday as a management adviser to Save Our Youth, <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a private umbrella group for several anti-drug projects. He will focus, to start with, on the `` Pipers'' initiative. Under an arrangement with the court, <PERSON> North </PERSON> will work in the program about 16 hours a week for 75 weeks. Early last month, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> Gerhard </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gesell </PERSON> sentenced North to two years' probation, a $ 150,000 fine and 1,200 hours of community service for his conviction on three felony counts in the Iran-Contra case North is appealing his conviction, but told the court he was eager to begin the community work. North, in a two-hour get-acquainted meeting with program organizers, was `` very excited about his involvement,'' coordinator <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said Tuesday. `` He wanted to get to work right away.'' North initially was scheduled to return to the program's offices at the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday afternoon, but <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said the second session was postponed to avoid the glare of media attention. <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said <PERSON> Gesell </PERSON> assigned <PERSON> North </PERSON> to the Save Our Youth program after the judge learned of the `` Pipers'' effort. The five men, all well-known in the drug community, will try to dissuade youngsters from using drugs and also will seek out dealers in efforts to give them legal employment, <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> `` </PERSON> <PERSON> Roach </PERSON>'' <PERSON> Henry </PERSON>, a member of the Pipers who met with <PERSON> North </PERSON> on Monday, said he has no qualms about working with the former <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> aide. `` He's interesting ... and I think he was interested in us,'' said <PERSON> Henry </PERSON>. `` I think he will use his mind to help us develop solutions.'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Staggers </PERSON>, chairman of Save Our Youth, said <PERSON> North </PERSON> `` represents one of the best minds in the nation when it comes to strategizing on how to attack problems.'' As a deputy on <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> staff, <PERSON> North </PERSON> not only was a key figure in the secret sale of arms to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> _ and diversion of profits to the Nicaraguan rebels _ but played a major role in planning the invasion of <LOCATION> Grenada </LOCATION>, the retaliatory bombing of <LOCATION> Libya </LOCATION> and the interception of an Egyptian airliner carrying the hijackers of the <PERSON> Achille </PERSON> <PERSON> Lauro </PERSON> cruise ship. Staggers and <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> acknowledged that <PERSON> North </PERSON>'s political image is a far cry from that favored by <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>'s black community. But `` we're creating a marriage of two extremes,'' said <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON>. `` The focus is not on our differences. The focus is on changing what is happening on our streets and to our young people. The young black man is self-destructive; he's becoming an endangered species,'' <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said. Under terms dictated by <PERSON> Gesell </PERSON>, <PERSON> North </PERSON> can not act as a fundraiser, can not counsel young people, and can not give speeches or act as a spokesman for the group. Thus, <PERSON> North </PERSON> will `` serve as a advisor in the management and administration of SOY's activities,'' with his initial focus on the Pipers, <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> said. `` He will stay in his element, and we'll stay in ours.''
