<HEAD>Democratic Fax Machine Alerts Media About Republican Robinson's Speech</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 9th graf, `He said...' to make clear that comment is from
Blakely.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SCOTT CHARTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Nearly two weeks after <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> defected to the Republicans, a facsimile machine belonging to the <ORGANIZATION> Arkansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> was used to publicize a speech he was to make. `` I see a little humor in that,'' <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> said Wednesday. A news release sent by fax to The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> on Monday said <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>, identified in the release as a Republican, would speak Wednesday at the <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Little </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rotary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION>. It said reporters could contact <PERSON> Kip </PERSON> <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> for more information and gave a telephone number. The number was for the headquarters of the state <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, where <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> is executive director. He is also in charge of Rotary Club publicity. <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> confirmed Wednesday that he sent the release. `` It really is a real deal. It did come from us. I'm a member of that club and on the board and one of my responsibilities is advising the press. We asked Congressman <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> about three months ago to come and speak to us,'' <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> switched from Democrat to Republican on July 28, saying he was no longer comfortable as a conservative southerner in his old party. <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> said he saw no problem with using a <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> fax machine to get news coverage for a Republican, and said he uses the machine to relay weekly releases about the <ORGANIZATION> Rotary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION>'s guest speakers to newsrooms in <LOCATION> Little </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rock </LOCATION>. `` It was not like it was long distance,'' <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> said, adding that there was no cost to the party for the local call. `` Certainly I appreciate the free publicity,'' <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> said, `` but I do n't know if that will put him in good standing with the Democrats. I think it's a very kind gesture on their part to let people know about my speech by way of their fax machine.'' `` I like <PERSON> Kip </PERSON> <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> and I do n't have anything against <ORGANIZATION> Arkansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democrats </ORGANIZATION>. One day they will make the same decision I have made,'' <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> said Wednesday. <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> was joshed by <PERSON> Ken </PERSON> <PERSON> Coon </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Arkansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. `` We make mistakes ourselves sometimes. I guess <PERSON> Kip </PERSON> secretly wants to change,'' <PERSON> Coon </PERSON> said with a laugh Wednesday. `` I appreciate the publicity. We need all the help we can get.'' <PERSON> Blakely </PERSON> said he joked about <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> during last week's Rotary meeting. `` Tongue in cheek, I stood up and asked Mr. President whether it would be the honorable thing for the congressman to address us since we scheduled him when he was with one party and switched to another,'' he said. On Tuesday, <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> was introduced to a meeting of civic clubs at <LOCATION> Benton </LOCATION> as: `` A Democrat, <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> ...'' The man giving the introduction said the information came directly from a biography supplied by <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>'s office. <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> replied with a grin: `` I will check with my staff when I get back to the office this afternoon about the bio they sent out.''
