<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 `` The Abyss'' could well be this summer's most ambitious, most problematic and, finally, most fascinating movie. `` The Abyss'' features no major stars, and while the rest of the film season has unfolded nearly seamlessly, this $ 43 million project was a magnet for miscues. It missed its original release date by a month, and because its rough cut ran 40 minutes long, a number of important expository and spectacular effects scenes were cut. But 20th Century <PERSON> Fox </PERSON>'s `` The Abyss'' finally arrived, opening Wednesday on 1,550 screens. The cast and crew of this technically uncompromising adventure movie endured 3 -LCB- months of principal filming, 40 percent of it underwater. It stars <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> -LRB- `` The Right Stuff'' -RRB- and <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Mastrantonio </PERSON> -LRB- `` January Man'' -RRB-. So elaborate is the film's look and sound that almost everyone from director <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Cameron </PERSON> to sound mixer <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Orloff </PERSON> labored seven days a week, every week, throughout the first half of 1989. The final print of `` The Abyss'' was completed just hours before its first media preview, on July 28. `` The ringing sound of hysteria was always just around the corner,'' said <PERSON> Cameron </PERSON>, the writer and director of such acclaimed and personal techno-thrillers as `` The Terminator'' and `` Aliens.'' `` It seems t cut is a crucial sequence explaining that the story's underwater aliens are worried about nuclear war. That's why the sub crashes, the hurricane suddenly materializes and a now deleted tidal-wave assault develops. `` <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> had a huge story to tell,'' <PERSON> Mastrantonio </PERSON> said. `` And there's a whole lot that's been cut. But given the time limitations of any normal film ... I think that he's told it cohesively.'' <PERSON> Cameron </PERSON> and <PERSON> Hurd </PERSON> say, too, they have succeeded in assembling a persuasive and cautionary tale about common people facing uncommon circumstances. `` A film should always try to take somebody somewhere, whether it's emotionally or physically transporting one to another place,'' <PERSON> Cameron </PERSON> said. `` I see this as much of an emotional journey as a physical one. `` The great thing about film is that you can really do anything. You can show the biggest, most spectacular thing in the world, and in the next split second you can focus down to the most microcosmic human moment. `` The ocean is for many people a great primal fear,'' the director said. `` It's a very powerful thing, it can be incredibly fickle _ weather and currents can turn on you instantly _ but it's also the source of life and a place of incredible wonder.
