<HEAD>Israeli Soldiers Kill Two During Protests, Third Arab Found Dead</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN RICE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli troops shot and killed a man and child in a Palestinian refugee camp Wednesday during demonstrations marking 20 months of the Arab rebellion, hospital officials said. A third <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> was found dead, and <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said he was killed by Israeli settlers. The deaths raised to 533 the number of Palestinians killed by <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers or settlers since the uprising began in the occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> in December 1987. Thirty-eight Israelis have died in the violence. Officials at <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> said 6-year-old <PERSON> Yousef </PERSON> <PERSON> Ghazi </PERSON> <PERSON> Salameh </PERSON> and 23-year-old <PERSON> Ziad </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Bannat </PERSON> were shot to death during daylong clashes in the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>'s Shati refugee camp. Hospital officials said <PERSON> Salameh </PERSON> was shot in the heart and quoted the boy's family as saying a soldier on a rooftop had fired at him. <PERSON> Bannat </PERSON> died later of gunshot wounds to the stomach and chest, the officials said. The army spokesman's office confirmed <PERSON> Salameh </PERSON>'s death but said he was 8. The office said <PERSON> Bannat </PERSON>'s body was taken from the hospital for burial before the army could confirm the cause of death and that it was checking further. Arab hospital reports said at least 19 Palestinians were wounded in Shati. Four other Palestianians were wounded elsewhere in the territories in clashes with <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> troops, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said. The army confirmed five wounded and said it was checking other reports. The riots at Shati occurred as Palestinians throughout the occupied lands mounted a gener