<HEAD>Survivors Tell of Thai Pirate Attack That Killed 71</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HARI S.MANIAM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Thai pirates took pleading Vietnamese refugees from the hold of a boat one by one, beat them with sticks and iron rods and then hacked them to death, survivors told refugee officials Wednesday. The officials said 71 Vietnamese were reported dead. The pirates sank the refugees' boat by ramming it twice with their own boat and then systematically killed survivors swimming in the sea, they added. <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Marie </PERSON> <PERSON> Fakhouri </PERSON>, chief representative in <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> for the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commissioner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Refugees </ORGANIZATION>, said 13 who survived were interviewed Wednesday by <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Malaysian </LOCATION> refugee officials and gave this account: Their boat left <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> on Thursday, Aug. 3, carrying 58 men, 15 women and 11 children. On Saturday night, two fishing boats intercepted them and towed them for some distance. Fishing crew boarded their boat and robbed them of their valuables. Some Vietnamese were transferred to the fishing boats. The rest were kept in the hold of the refugee boat. The fishermen-pirates then brought up men singly from the hold, clubbed them and then killed them with axes, the refugee officials said. The men cried and pleaded, but the pirates, whom they ascertained to be Thais because of their appearance and language, showed no mercy. `` In the panic that followed, others tried to storm out of the hold, but were contained by the pirates, who tied fishing nets over the opening. The trapped men then tried to cut their way through the nets without success,'' <PERSON> Fakhouri </PERSON> reported, quoting the survivors. He said the ramming, sinking and killing of Vietnamese in the water followed, but 13 survived by swimming to an oil rig, where w