 behind <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. Tuesday's report says the disinvestment campaign has had more success in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> than in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> in part because municipal and educational bodies have threatened to cancel large contracts if companies did not sever their South African ties.
