. In all, the government has estimated the First RepublicBank rescue will cost $ 3 billion. Improved profits at the <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> institution led to <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION>'s decision to move up its purchase, the bank said last month. <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> earned $ 63.1 million in the second quarter, with $ 28.8 million going to <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Analysts said the buyout also removes some potential roadblocks to <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> acquiring other banks or thrifts as the state's troubled financial industry is cleaned Since entering the <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> market, <ORGANIZATION> NCNB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has sold $ 410 million worth of additional stock and seen its stock price climb to over $ 54 a share, more than double its share price on July 29, 1988, when the <ORGANIZATION> FDIC </ORGANIZATION> announced the deal.
