<HEAD>Harris Corp. Announces Plans to Sell Data, Computer Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Harris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> is seeking buyers for its data communications and personal computer divisions after an $ 85.2 million restructuring intended to streamline operations, the defense and aerospace contractor said Wednesday. The company, which began to scale down in the mid 1980s, is now organized into four major sectors: electronics, semiconductors, communications and <ORGANIZATION> Lanier </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Worldwide </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the new name of its Harris-3M international division. `` The businesses we are selling are outside the mainstream of our future interests, and their sale will release assets and other resources for ... our core businesses,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hartley </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer, in a press release. The release did not name a price for the two divisions or whether any companies have expressed interest in them. The restructuring cost dropped net income for the year ended June 30 nearly 80 percent, while sales and per-share profit rose. For the 12 months ended June 30, the Melbourne-based company reported net income of $ 21.3 million, or 55 cents a share, on sales of $ 2.2 billion, compared with net income of $ 100.5 million, or $ 2.50 a share, on sales of $ 1.8 billion for the previous fiscal year. In the fourth quarter, the restructuring costs led to a net loss of $ 52 million on sales of $ 768.3 million, compared with net income of $ 1.8 million, or 5 cents a share, on sales of $ 471.8 million in the year-ago period. In June, <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> pleaded no contest to filing inflated statements on behalf of a Filipino businessman convicted of defrauding the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> agreed to pay $ 200,000 in fines and $ 300,000 to settle civil claims against it arising from a <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> investigation of fraud involving weapons sales to the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>.
